    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a mechanically sorted 2003 BMW M3 (E46) finished in Carbon Black. This example features the S54 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six, renowned for its individual throttle bodies and 8,000 RPM redline. Power is delivered through a precise Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox to a limited-slip M-Variable differential. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including a comprehensive VANOS system overhaul and a reinforced rear subframe to ensure chassis rigidity under high lateral loads. The valvetrain is quiet following a recent shim adjustment, and the cooling system has been refreshed with a high-flow aluminum radiator. While the exterior shows minor road-derived patina, the suspension geometry remains true with upgraded polyurethane bushings and refreshed dampers. This is a high-revving, analog driver\u2019s car optimized for performance-oriented longevity.",
